    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown. Each figure shows a toy with four pieces labeled A through D. A pair of axes indicates that x is in the horizontal direction and y is in the vertical direction. Figure 1 is comprised of four sections that meet at a common point at the center of the figure. Piece A is at the top and has mass m, Piece B is to the right and has mass 3 m, Piece C is at the bottom and has mass 2 m, and Piece D is to the left and has mass 4 m. Figure 2 shows the same four pieces, but they are being moved apart from the center. Piece A is moving upward, piece B is moving to the right, piece C is moving downward, and piece D is moving to the left.\" src=\"/images/8d9da4c0dfb5557f5ac9a818680ddfe9.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A toy is made up of four pieces, with the relative masses indicated in the top-view figures shown. The toy is initially at rest on a horizontal surface, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. A mechanism internal to the toy causes the four pieces to move apart, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>. Friction between the pieces of the toy and the surface is negligible. Which of the following indicates an equation or set of equations that correctly describes the magnitudes of the momenta of the four pieces?</p>\n",
